<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you did everything right but no bonus, contact Binance support. Send them screenshots and details.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">What Is Binance Referral Program?</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Binance referral program is just Binance’s way of rewarding people for bringing in new users. You share your code, someone signs up with it, and both of you get something out of it. The new user might get a signup bonus, a fee discount, or a voucher they can use when trading. The inviter gets rewards too, basically for helping Binance grow its user base.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At the end of the day, it’s a growth tool. Binance ties rewards directly to user activity, so current members have a reason to tell their friends, and newcomers get a small financial boost for starting out. </span></p>
<h3><b>Where To Find My Binance Invitation Code?</b></h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-192498" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Where-To-Find-My-Binance-Invitation-Code.jpg" alt="Where To Find My Binance Invitation Code" width="1600" height="864" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Every Binance account comes with an invitation code. It’s automatic—you don’t have to request it. If you want to share it, here’s how you actually find it:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Log into the website, head over to the </span><b>User Center</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and click on [</span><b>Referral]</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Your personal code will show up there along with a referral link. Most people just share the link, since it already has the code built in.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">One thing to keep in mind: Binance only gives you one code. It doesn’t change unless Binance decides to overhaul the program. So once you know where to look, you don’t need to go hunting for new ones each time.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance Exchange Overview</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Founded in 2017, </span><a href="http://www.binance.com" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has grown into the world’s biggest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume. It handles millions of transactions every day and lists hundreds of coins, from the obvious ones like Bitcoin (BTC) and Ethereum (ETH) to plenty of smaller, less-known tokens. The point is, you get a lot of choice if you’re looking to trade or invest.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here’s what you can actually do on Binance:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Spot and Futures Trading:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Spot trading is the basic buy-and-sell of crypto. If you want to go further, Binance offers Futures contracts with leverage (up to 125x). There are USD-M and Coin-M contracts depending on how you want to trade.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Margin Trading:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> This lets you borrow money from Binance to boost your position. On Binance the leverage for margin is up to 5x your collateral. It’s riskier but useful for experienced traders.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Staking &amp; Earn:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Binance lets you earn interest on coins you’re just holding. Some assets have fixed terms, others are flexible. Rates depend on the token.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>P2P Trading:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> You can trade directly with other people for fiat currencies. Binance acts as the middle layer and holds the funds in escrow until both sides confirm. There are 100+ supported currencies and a wide range of payment methods.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>NFT Marketplace:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Binance runs an NFT market where you can buy, sell, or trade digital collectibles. It’s powered by BNB Chain and often features new artists and collections.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Binance Visa Card:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> You can spend your crypto directly with this card. Works at millions of merchants worldwide, just like a regular Visa.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Binance Charity:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Binance also has a non-profit arm that supports global charitable projects. Donations are tracked on-chain for transparency.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And that’s not even everything. The platform keeps adding more services, but these are the main ones most users rely on.</span></p>
<h3><b>Binance Trading Fees</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance charges fees anytime you trade, but they’re lower than a lot of other exchanges. For spot trades, the base fee is 0.1% maker / 0.1% taker. That’s the default rate for regular users.</span></p>
